snippet.title: Heineken's 147 years of making beer in Amsterdam
snippet.description: Road Trip 2011: Many visitors to the Dutch capital can't leave without taking in the Heineken Experience, a self-guided tour through the old Heineken brewery and a chance to see how the world-famous beer is made.

snippet.title: Amsterdam offcially approves new Airbnb-friendly laws
snippet.description: Hosts can now rent out their homes periodically, if they follow all the tax and safety laws related to vacation rentals.

snippet.title: Tell the time with the faces of Doctor Who
snippet.description: It's 10 minutes till Tom Baker! A watch-face app for Pebble indicates the time of day with the faces of the Doctor.

snippet.title: Ban lifted! It's time for 'Doctor Who' Lego
snippet.description: Whovians, start building your best Tardis. Lego Cuusoo relaxes its ban on "Doctor Who" fan-submitted projects.

snippet.title: Outrun daleks in the Doctor Pacman Flash game
snippet.description: Gobble up enough points before the colored daleks kill you in this fan-made game that pays tribute to both Doctor Who and Pac-Man. No word on any Ms. Pac-Man companions.

snippet.title: Peter Capaldi is new 'Doctor Who' star
snippet.description: Peter Capaldi has been named as the 12th Doctor, replacing Matt Smith in classic British sci-fi series.

snippet.title: Get Peter Capaldi's 'Doctor Who' stare with 'Capaldeyes'
snippet.description: Lash out at the next Doctor by printing out Peter Capaldi's intense glare in time for the "Doctor Who: Time of the Doctor" Christmas special.

snippet.title: Adorable amigurumi 'Doctor Who' dolls charm fans
snippet.description: Exterminknit! Artist Allison Hoffman crafts dolls not only of Time Lords, but also of their companions, villains, and the Tardis itself.

snippet.title: Doctor Who 50th anniversary special trailers revealed
snippet.description: The BBC has revealed two trailers for the upcoming special, which will air on 23 November at 7:50pm.

snippet.title: Become the Doctor with Sonic Screwdriver app
snippet.description: The BBC has released an official augmented-reality Sonic Screwdriver app, with four different versions of the screwdriver to choose from.
